items.name: Map A1
items.fluff:
I will dream of this pool until my dying days. We spilled the blood of three peoples to reach it, and though my steps left bloody footprints, no taint of gor touched its waters.

In every mirror I see my reflection in its surface, and the faces of the foes who sought to keep me from it. The Lady was with me that day, and ever since.

Baron Siclebald of Keldonne

items.name: Map A2
items.fluff:
These soft borderlanders knew of our approach when their fields burned and their herds scattered before us.

They even mounted a pitiful resistance, loosing arrows from roofs and thickets. Yet we poured from hill and forest and fell upon their hamlet.

So we took all that they had, and more than they could spare. None will stand between me and my glory - or my Lord’s.

Tolomeo “Shieldcleaver” - Chosen Warrior of Sugulag

items.name: Map A3
items.fluff:
We who know the true power behind the world must often work insecret.

With only a little persuasion, the former occupants were kind enough to allow this master of mysticism to set up home.

Now the estate is inhabited by friends ofmine, and our occasional... guests.

Fortunately, their arrival goes unnoticed in this grand place. Once the Courtesan arrives, the city will have such havoc visited upon it, they shall be gifted glorious visions of a new world.

Balthazar the Magnificent, servant of the Seven

items.name: Map A4
items.fluff:
In the mountains of the Blasted Plains, water is avaluable resource. Even the water to be found in avolcanic caldera can beput to good use.

Now these interlopers would seek to infringe upon lands we hold by divine right?

By force of arms they will learn their error. By steel and discipline they will be driven from this place. By fire will our retribution be delivered to them.

Prophet Tevika of the Gar
Shakhub Citadel

items.name: Map A5
items.fluff:
You do not see us, but we see you - uninitiated. You tramp the highlands and bring waste and decay - despoilers.

We lie in wait, beneath the surface, and still your eyes fail you - hotbloods.

We will strike from bush,from swamp, from grass, silent death comes - prey.

We mourn your passing, yet your graves will give new life from decay - renewers.

Skink Captain Akeakami

items.name: Map A6
items.fluff:
Once our walls stood highand proud over the city of Khedesai. Centuries of wind and sand have created breaches that no battering ram ever did.

You saw our unmanned walls and thought our history was yours for the taking. Our legacy there to be plundered.

We rose from our eternal rest. Took up weapons that survived the ages. Set ourselves to defend our home. And drove the living from our hallowed ground.

Death Hierarch Nehi

items.name: Map A7
items.fluff:
Above all, our people survive on their discipline.

Some will speak of guns and artillery. They have not seen damp powder or misfires. Some will speak of arms and armour.

They have not seen swords break. Some will talk of faith. I honour Sunna, but she will not defend us - we must fight in her name.

Discipline holds us together, binds us to our cause. The Beacons are a symbol of our commitment, and we will defend them!

Marshall Hugo Hafer

items.name: Map A8
items.fluff:
In the truly wild places, few make their home. As we travel the DarkWoods, we know all the denizens beneath the black boughs.

Through the tangled thickets and dire beasts, the Witch’s story is known to all our people in this land. From her cabin, the Witch sees all, and we respect her wisdom and her trade in herbs - and ales.

Now interlopers walk beneath the canopy, among her gardens, and we will drive them backonce more. That her story may continue, and that we may tell it anew.

Soothsayer Bremen

items.name: Map B1
items.fluff:
Many who are talented in the Art choose to reside in our great institutions. Asfada and Canrac offer unparalleled opportunities for magical study. Yet many choose tobuild their own towers in isolation, preferring seclusion while hoarding secrets.

The home of Mage Ilthuryn is one such location. An imposing holdfast of white stone, set in a hollow with a still pool of silvery water.

Now that home is under attack from invaders, and we are mustered to defend the Master Mage. Let nothing stand in our way. For Celeda Ablan!

Warden of the Flame
Civessin Eilynore

items.name: Map B2
items.fluff:
The nobles of Dathen take great pride in their majestic estates, displays of their position and standing.

The villa of Prince Folmon Perxina is no exception. He commands one of the grandest manors to be found, with extensive grounds spreading out across the landscape.

It is known that beasts trained in the Menagerie roam the holdings, tasked with savaging any who would dare to transgress.

The Prince’s personal guard represents a veritable army, and this is the force you now find yourself in service to. Serve well, and you may secure advancement.

Dread Sergeant
Trabhræn Crislain

items.name: Map B3
items.fluff:
Among the peaks and valleys of the White Mountains, there are many remnants of bastions which once marked frontiers of our Holds.

The crumbling walls and slopes of Dun Kenaz are one such example. This was once a thriving stronghold, home to a hundred of our kin and a stopping point for those who traversed this mountain pass.

I dream that one day thefort will be restored, that the walls can be repaired and the flooded courtyard drained and relaid.

For now though, I pledge to ensure no others desecrate the memories of those who died and were buried beneath this place.

Thane Bodraz
Bronzespine

items.name: Map B4
items.fluff:
On the border of the Steppe and Tsuandan, the locals know they owe tribute to the Great Khan. Food grown along the border will feed our tribe through the harsh winter.

Where there is value,there are thieves. Now they set upon our people,and we must drive the wolves back. Longjing’s people often press along our border, but when they threaten our sustenance, they will taste our wrath.

Call in the tribe, ready the cannons, and prepare the beasts.

Khan Jetei

items.name: Map B5
items.fluff:
In times long past, our reach extended across most of the known world. The Awakening set us as the inheritors of Avras, and all its glory.

When we were forced to abandon our birthright, our people found havens in many places beneath the notice of those who thought us dispatched.

This watchtower once stood on the fringes of our territory, in what was the Regio Equitatem. The horselords who rule these lands now see a mere husk of a structure, with no clue of the strength positioned within. These seeds lie in many places, and wait our moment to rise again.

Senator Mettius Sigilis

items.name: Map B6
items.fluff:
Ours is the tree, the thicket, the forest. Ours is the wilderness, the sylvan lands, the liminal places.

Yours are the villages, the towns, the cities. The foolhardy attempt to have nature follow lines and squares.

We see you from our home. For so long as you keep a distance we tolerate. But transgress once too often, and you may find the forest draws near. Nothing built by mortals cannot be undone by nature and time.

Druid Narycot

items.name: Map B7
items.fluff:
Rest in peace. A quaint notion. To lay the body to rest, to bury all the infinite possibilities in the ground, for worms and maggots to feast.

You fear my kind. Our knowledge scares you, as does our strength and will to use it. Here, in this quiet hamlet, I have everything I need to build an army.

The souls of your dead, will provide my soldiers. Your cattle will fall and my zombies will rise.

And buried somewhere in the nearby hills, I have heard tell of a dragon’s fallen form. Soon, I will be among the great powers, all beginning from a small town graveyard. Rest in peace? You may try…

Zakutnik the Necromancer

items.name: Map B8
items.fluff:
We cross the bridge, we take the town, we win the game, we take the loot, we keep moving.

Now peaceborn want to stop us. Break their own bridge. Think Warborn can’t swim? Think goblins not make bridges? We can’t build boats?

Extra challenge for all this time. Maybe some are returned to the Sleep, and we wait to see them again.

But we are not easy stopped. We will break walls, show strength, win with cunning. We are born of war, and this will be best war yet!

Warboss Urbul

items.name: Map 1 - Clearwater Springs
items.fluff: Not all the Broken Isles are inhabitable, but most are thanks to an abundance of natural springs – even on islands without lakes or rivers. Several springs, such as that of the Temple of Serena in Patmos, are considered sacred by the locals.

items.name: Map 2 - Ancient Fortifications
items.fluff: The Broken Isles have been fought over throughout all nine ages, seeing many empires come and go. Ancient ruins are more common here than almost anywhere else in the world, and many are surrounded by the remains of earthen banks, ditches, or crumbing walls that once served as defenses. The grandiose, Golden Age ruins of Dhimkalos are said to be particularly impressive.

items.name: Map 3 - Dormant Caldera
items.fluff: Much of the region is volcanically active, and some crater-shaped islands bear the telltale signs of ancient eruptions. Some calderas contain pools or lakes after stormy weather, as well as the remains of those who have attempted to settle the summit. The legendary site of Ulxis is perhaps the best-known example – though its Oracle and her cult remain there to this day.

items.name: Map 4 – Abandoned Settlement
items.fluff: The most impressive ruins can be quite extensive, indicating a former city or important port. These sites often demonstrate habitation across different eras. The ongoing excavation of Taynagrit by archaeologists from Sonnstahl has so far revealed temples, halls and even pyramids from distinct ages, all atop an elven city from the Golden Age.

items.name: Map 5 – Historic Battlefield
items.fluff: Certain parts of an island’s terrain present natural arenas or unique opportunities for bringing armies to battle. Many commanders – knowingly or not – find themselves fighting atop the bones of fallen warriors from ancient wars. The city of Mykleos was famously the site of a long siege that has since passed into myth and song, with many legendary battles having been fought in the surrounding region.

items.name: Map 6 – Mountainous Crags
items.fluff: As their name suggests, the Broken Isles are known for rough, jagged terrain, making for impassable coastlines, spectacular peaks and dizzying cliffs. Some of the most remarkable sites from antiquity have been discovered atop mountains or within hidden passes between the crags – such as the renowned Cairn of Mileusa, a huge mound of stones dedicated to a namless champion of long ago.

items.name: Spoils of War
items.description:
Setup during Pre-game Selections: None.
Rules:When an enemy unit is Destroyed in Combat, the opposing player puts one Spoils Token on one of their Scoring Units (if there are any) that was just engaged with the unit Destroyed in Combat. A unit loses all of its Spoils Tokens when any of the following occurs:
• The last Health Point on its Rank-and-File models is lost.
• It becomes Shaken. Remember that units that perform a Flee Move automatically become Shaken.
Winning conditions: At the end of the game, the player with the most Spoils Token on their units wins this Primary Objective.

items.name: Breakthrough
items.description:
Setup during Pre-game Selections: Mark Deployment Zones.
Rules: None.
Winning conditions: At the end of the game, each player adds together the number of Scoring Units in their opponent’s Deployment Zone and the number of enemy units that were Scoring at the start of the game that were Destroyed in Combat. The player with the highest total wins the Primary Objective.

items.name: Secure Target
items.description:
Setup during Pre-game Selections: Place 2 markers with their centers on the line dividing the board into halves (the dashed line in the figures describing Deployment Types), one on each side of the centre of the table, as close as possible to a third of the length of the long Board Edge (24″ on a 72″ wide board) away from it, and more than 1″ away from Impassable Terrain.
Rules: A marker is controlled by the player with the most expensive Scoring Units within 12″ of the centre of the marker (if both players have Scoring Units with identical Points Cost, no one controls it).
Winning conditions: At the end of Game Turns 3–6, a Victory Counter is awarded to a Player which controls an Objective. The player with the most such Victory Counters at the end of the game wins this Primary Objective.

items.name: Forage and Plunder
items.description:
Setup during Pre-game Selections:Nominate a total of three different Terrain Features: The Terrain Features closest to the centre of the Battlefield. Then both players nominate a not already nominated Terrain Feature that is fully outside their own Deployment Zone they may nominate the same. Impassable Terrain and Walls cannot be nominated.
Rules: You automatically plunder a nominated Terrain Feature, that you have not already plundered, when a friendly Scoring Units starts 6 in contact with it during your Player Turn 3-6. Both players can plunder all nominated Terrain Features once, even if the other player has already done so.
Winning conditions: At the end of the game, if one player has plundered more nominated Terrain Features than the other player they win this Primary Objective.

items.name: Hold the Centre
items.description:
Setup during Pre-game Selections: Mark the centre of the table.
Rules: The battlefield is controlled by the player with the most expensive Scoring Units within 12″ of the centre of the table (if both players have Scoring Units with identical Points Cost, no one controls it).
Winning conditions: At the end of Game Turns 3–6, a Victory Counter is awarded to a Player who controls at least one marker. The player with the most such Victory Counters at the end of the game wins this Primary Objective.

items.name: Hidden Agendas
items.description:
Setup during Pre-game Selections: None.
Rules: None.
Winning conditions: Winning a Secondary Objective is worth +/-2 Battle Points. This replaces the normal Battle Points bonus for winning Primary and Secondary Objectives.

items.name: Capture the Flags
items.description:
Setup during Pre-game Selections: None.
Rules: None.
Winning conditions: At the end of the game, you win this Secondary Objective if you have more Standard Bearers and Battle Standard Bearers on the Battlefield, than the opponent has.

items.name: Commit to Battle
items.description:
Setup during Pre-game Selections: Mark the opponent’s Deployment Zone.
Rules: None.
Winning conditions: At the end of the game, you win this Secondary Objective if you have more Scoring Units in your opponent’s Deployment Zone than the opponent has (in their own Deployment Zone).

items.name: Demonstrate Superiority
items.description:
Setup during Pre-game Selections: The opponent nominates one of their units. If possible, this must be the most expensive Scoring Unit.
Rules: None.
Winning conditions: At the end of the game, you win this Secondary Objective if the nominated unit has been destroyed.

items.name: Enslave and Ransom
items.description:
Setup during Pre-game Selections: None.
Rules: You gain an Enslaved Counter each time an enemy unit is Destroyed in Combat.
If the unit is Destroyed in step 5 of the Round of Combat sequence (Breaking and Pursuing) you gain an additional Enslaved Counter. This includes failing a Break Test and being caught or dying during the Flee Move, Supernal unit failing a Break Test or Unstable unit losing a Combat and being wiped due to HP loss. This does not include units being destroyed as a direct result of Melee Attacks. Ignore Attachable Models joined to units with Rank-and-File models.
Winning conditions: At the end of the game, you win this Secondary Objective if you have at least four Enslaved Counters.

items.name: Master the Veil
items.description:
Setup during Pre-game Selections: Mark the centre of the table.
Rules: None.
Winning conditions: At the end of the game, you win this Secondary Objective if you have a model with Channel, or that knows a spell (Learned Spell or Bound Spell), within 12″ of the centre of table, and the opponent has not.

items.name: Forbid Trespass
items.description:
Setup during Pre-game Selections: You nominate a Terrain Feature on the Battlefield that is more than 12″ away from any Table Edge, other than Impassable Terrain.
Rules: A nominated Terrain Feature is plundered when an enemy Scoring Unit starts any of its Player Turn 3–6 in contact with it.
Winning conditions: At the end of the game, you win this Secondary Objective if the nominated Terrain Feature was not plundered.

items.name: Seize and Secure
items.description:
Setup during Pre-game Selections: The opponent nominates a Terrain Feature on the Battlefield that is more than 12″ away from any Table Edge. Impassable Terrain cannot be nominated.
Rules: A nominated Terrain Feature is plundered when a friendly Scoring Unit starts any of its Player Turn 3–6 in contact with it.
Rules: A nominated Terrain Feature is plundered when an enemy Scoring Unit starts any of its Player Turn 3–6 in contact with it.
Winning conditions: At the end of the game, you win this Secondary Objective if the nominated Terrain Feature was plundered.

items.name: Settle the Score
items.description:
Setup during Pre-game Selections: The opponent nominates one of their units. If possible, this must be the most expensive non-Scoring Unit.
Rules: A nominated Terrain Feature is plundered when a friendly Scoring Unit starts any of its Player Turn 3–6 in contact with it.
Rules: None.
Winning conditions: At the end of the game, you win this Secondary Objective, if the nominated unit has been destroyed.

items.name: Slay the Beast
items.description:
Setup during Pre-game Selections: The opponent nominates one of their units. If possible, this must be the unit in the Army List with the largest HP / model ratio.
Rules: None.
Winning Conditions:At the end of the game, you win this Secondary Objective, if the nominated unit has been destroyed.

items.name: Stand Firm
items.description:
Setup during Pre-game Selections: Mark your Deployment Zone.
Rules: None.
Winning Conditions:At the end of the game, you win this Secondary Objective if you have more Scoring Units in your Deployment Zone than the opponent has (in your Deployment Zone).

items.name: Unleash the Big Guns
items.description:
Setup during Pre-game Selections: You nominate two Terrain Features on the Battlefield that are not fully within your Deployment Zone. Impassable Terrain and Walls cannot be nominated. Then mark up all non-Characters units from your Army List that have Shooting Weapons and one Scoring unit without Shooting Weapons. Finally, if less than five units have been marked, you may mark one additional Scoring Unit.
Rules:
Winning Conditions: non-Shaken makred unit in both nominated Terrain Features.

items.name: Work as One
items.description:
Setup during Pre-game Selections: Mark the centre of the table.
Rules: None.
Winning Conditions:At the end of the game, you win this Secondary Objective if you have more Scoring Units within 9″ of the centre of table than the opponent has.

options.name: Trusted Adviser
options.description: When an army that includes a Trusted Adviser is about to roll for which Secondary Objective to play, roll twice, and if a duplicate is rolled, roll again until two different Secondary Objectives have been randomised. After this, the player with the Trusted Adviser may select which of these Secondary Objectives is played.

options.name: Glory Hunter
options.description:
When Choosing Weapons and Equipment, if the model’s unit is Engaged with an enemy unit that contains a Character, it must issue a “Duel”. The opponent may either accept or refuse the Duel. If refused; the model that issued the Duel gains +1 to their side’s Combat Score this Round of Combat. If accepted; the opponent selects a Character in a unit Engaged with the model that issued the Duel. Apply the following rules to the two models: “Duellists” (the model issuing the Duel, and the model chosen to accept the Duel) during this Round of Combat.

• Other models may not allocate StandardMelee Attacks towards the Duellists.
• The Duellists are considered to be in base contact with each other.
• The Duellists must allocate theirStandardMelee Attacks towards each other (even if their models are not physically in contact).
• Other Melee Attacks, such as Grind Attacks, Impact Hitsand Stomp Attacks, follow their normal rules for allocation.
• If either or both Duellists causes the last HP loss to the opposing Duellist, it has won the Duel. The winner(s) counts as having successfully accomplished their Secondary Objective.

If both players have models with Glory Hunter, whose units are Engaged, the Active Player must issue a Duel with their model with Glory Hunter, and the Reactive Player must accept the Duel with their model with Glory Hunter.

options.name: Curse of Lycanthropy
options.description: One use only. Duration: One Turn. You may activate this ability when Choosing Equipment and Abilities. Set the model part’s: Att to 4, Str to 5, and AP to 3. The model part also gains Regeneration (4+) and Innate Weapons. Whilst active the model part can only use Innate Weapons.

items.name: Assassination
items.fluff: The enemy look to their champions for courage. Identify and eliminate them with extreme prejudice.

objectives.description: Each time an enemy CHARACTER model is destroyed.
One or more enemy CHARACTER models were destroyed this turn.
All CHARACTER models from your opponent’s army have been destroyed during the battle.

items.name: Behind enemy lines
items.fluff: Break through the foe’s army and cut off their lines of escape.

objectives.description: One unit from your army (excluding AIRCRAFT and Battle-shocked units) is wholly within your opponent’s deployment zone.
Two or more units from your army (excluding AIRCRAFT and Battle-shocked units) are wholly within your opponent’s deployment zone.

items.name: Bring it down
items.fluff: The opposing army contains numerous heavily armoured units. Take any opportunity to bring them down.

objectives.description: Each time an enemy MONSTER or VEHICLE unit is destroyed.
The total of the Wounds characteristics of the models in that destroyed unit was 15+ (at its Starting Strength).
The total of the Wounds characteristics of the models in that destroyed unit was 20+ (at its Starting Strength).
The above VP are cumulative, so destroying a MONSTER or VEHICLE unit with a combined Wounds characteristic of 20 would award you 6VP.

items.name: Storm hostile objective
items.fluff: Dominate the field of battle. Storm every site of tactical import and leave the foe with no place to hide.

objectives.description: You control one or more objective markers that were controlled by your opponent at the start of the turn.
Your opponent did not control any objective markers at the start of the turn, and you control one or more objective markers that you did not control at the start of the turn.

items.name: Cull the horde
items.fluff: The enemy come forth in teeming masses. Their ranks must be thinned if the day is to be won.

objectives.description:
Each time an enemy INFANTRY unit is destroyed, if one or more of the following conditions are satisfied:
- The Starting Strength of the destroyed unit was 20+.
- The total of the Wounds characteristics of the models in the destroyed unit was 25+ (at its Starting Strength).
- When that unit’s player added that unit to their army, the points value they subtracted from the total permitted for this battle was sufficient for that unit to be composed of 20 or more models.

items.name: Recover assets
items.fluff: Scattered strategic assets must be swiftly reclaimed.

objectives.description: Two of your units recovered assets this turn.
Three of your units recovered assets this turn.

items.name: Area denial
items.fluff: It is critical that this area is dominated. No enemy vanguard or guerrilla units can be allowed to disrupt our plans.

objectives.description: One or more units from your army (excluding AIRCRAFT and Battle-shocked units) are within 3" of the centre of the battlefield, and there are no enemy units within 3" of the centre of the battlefield.
One or more units from your army (excluding AIRCRAFT and Battle-shocked units) are within 3" of the centre of the battlefield, and there are no enemy units within 6" of the centre of the battlefield.

items.name: Defend stronghold
items.fluff: You are charged with the defence of a key objective. It must not be permitted to fall into enemy hands.

objectives.description: You control one or more objective markers in your deployment zone.

items.name: Sabotage
items.fluff: This region is replete with strategic assets or supply caches vital to the foe. See to it that they are reduced to just so much flaming wreckage.

objectives.description: Your unit committed sabotage this turn and is not within your opponent’s deployment zone.
Your unit committed sabotage this turn and is within your opponent’s deployment zone.

items.name: Cleanse
items.fluff: The objectives in this area have been tainted and must be cleansed with ritual and purifying flame.

objectives.description: One objective marker was cleansed by your army this turn.
Two or more objective markers were cleansed by your army this turn.

items.name: Overwhelming force
items.fluff: Scour the enemy from the face of the battlefield.

objectives.description: Each time an enemy unit that started the turn within range of an objective marker is destroyed.

items.name: Engage on all fronts
items.fluff: This area is of extreme importance. You are to lead an immediate all-out assault to capture it and deny it to our enemy for good.

objectives.description: One or more units from your army (excluding AIRCRAFT and Battle-shocked units) are wholly within three different table quarters, and those units are all more than 6" away from the centre of the battlefield.

One or more units from your army (excluding AIRCRAFT and Battle-shocked units) are wholly within four different table quarters, and those units are all more than 6" away from the centre of the battlefield.

items.name: Establish locus
items.fluff: Whether a teleport homer crackling with arcane energies, a daemonic summoning circle, a pheromonal marker or some other means of guiding forces onto the battlefield, this locus must be set up swiftly to pave the road to victory.

objectives.description: Your unit established a locus this turn and is within 6" of the centre of the battlefield.
Your unit established a locus this turn and is within your opponent’s deployment zone.

items.name: Secure no man’s land
items.fluff: You must advance swiftly into no man’s land and seize it before the enemy can, lest they take control of the entire battlefield.

objectives.description: You control one objective marker in No Man’s Land.
You control two or more objective markers in No Man’s Land.

items.name: Marked for death
items.fluff: These specific enemy assets must be eliminated to ensure victory, no matter how insignificant they might seem.

objectives.description: One or more of the selected units were destroyed (or removed from the battlefield for any other reason) this turn.

items.name: No prisoners
items.fluff: Exterminate your enemies.

objectives.description: Each time an enemy unit is destroyed.

items.name: Extend battle lines
items.fluff: The battleground is conquered one yard at a time. Press forward to establish a strong military presence in the area.

objectives.description: You control one or more objective markers within your deployment zone and one or more objective markers within No Man’s Land.
You only have one unit on the battlefield, and that unit controls one objective marker within No Man’s Land.
